            {
                "description": "Once the noodles are done cooking. Pour a baking pan about 1/4 full with meat + sauce. Add a full layer of noodles on top of sauce in the baking pan. Then add cheese on top of the noodles. Repeat until the baking pan is nearly full minus about 1/4&quote;, making sure that cheese is the top layer. Add an even coating of parmesan cheese."
            },
            {
                "description": "Cover the baking pan with cooking foil, folding in the middle to ensure air can pass through. Place the baking pan in the oven and cook for 30 minutes."
            },
            {
                "description": "After 30 minutes, remove the cooking foil from the baking pan and continue cooking for an additional 20 minutes. Alternatively you can cook until the desired crispness of the cheese on top, which usually turns an even golden color on top."
            },
            {
                "description": "Remove and let sit for a minute or two before serving."
